<TITLE> Dulal remanded in 2001 Malibagh shooting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com)- Dulal Mia, arrested on charges of shooting and killing four persons in a BNP procession at Malibagh in the capital in 2001, has been remanded for four days. The investigation officer, sub-inspector Ahsanul Haque, took Dulal to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court, Dhaka and prayed for a 10- day remand. Magistrate ABM Abul Fattah granted four days. Four persons were killed when shots were fired into a procession of the BNP from a procession led by Awami League leader HBM Iqbal during a hartal programme of the then opposition February 13, 2001. Dulal was arrested in Mogh Bazar area Saturday night in connection with the incident. Following the incident, pictures of Dulal, pistol in hand, were published in different newspapers. bdnews24.
